feat(api): :sparkles: add per-IP rate limiting middleware

Why:
The API lacks protection against abuse and resource exhaustion.
Without rate limiting, a single client can make unlimited requests,
degrading service for all users and increasing infrastructure costs.

What:
Add configurable per-IP rate limiting middleware using a sliding
window algorithm backed by Redis. Defaults to 100 requests per
15-minute window. Returns 429 Too Many Requests with Retry-After
header when limit is exceeded. Fully tested and integrated into
Express app initialization.

Ticket: PROJ-312
Signed-off-by: Alice Developer <alice@example.com>
